The brave and wise man, who intends to overcome his foes, must first of all
strive to subdue the internal enemies of his own heart and mind, and the
members of his own body. ...

The kings of the earth in their earthly capitals are not as happy as are the
lords of the cities of their own bodies, and the masters of their own minds.
